When writing about command line switches in a man page, care must be
taken to escape all minus signs to prevent them from being interpreted
as dashes by groff.

This patch fixes a couple such problems in the scrotwm man page.
Index: trunk/scrotwm.1
===================================================================
--- trunk.orig/scrotwm.1	2009-10-03 21:01:17.000000000 +0200
+++ trunk/scrotwm.1	2009-10-03 21:03:02.000000000 +0200
@@ -191,7 +191,7 @@
 .It Cm initscr
 initscreen.sh
 .It Cm menu
-dmenu_run -fn $bar_font -nb $bar_color -nf $bar_font_color -sb $bar_border -sf $bar_color
+dmenu_run \-fn $bar_font \-nb $bar_color \-nf $bar_font_color \-sb $bar_border \-sf $bar_color
